<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - OIL COOLER and FILTER HOUSING - Cleaning, Inspection, and Testing
        - Oil Cooler Leaks
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="S3509001" svcproctype="test" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Oil Cooler Leaks</title>
        <figure id="f2650915" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d1362.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 342. Air pressure leakage test</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air pressure regulator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air adapter (make locally)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Cooler Pressure Test Plate</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The oil filter base must be installed on the oil cooler cover assembly before a pressure test can
                    done.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten Oil Cooler Pressure Test Plate to oil cooler.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install air pressure gauge to EGR cooler coolant outlet port.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spray soapy water around the oil cooler and oil filter base.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not submerge into water. Submerging could allow water to be
                    introduced into oil passages, causing engine damage during initial startup.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 207 kPa (30 psi) of air pressure.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If leaking, bubbles will be present between the oil cooler and cover. Replace assembly as
                required.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove soapy water residue. Blow off with compressed air.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
